oakcurric:unit-2865
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Historical events: perfect tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "historical-events-perfect-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils consolidate the perfect tense with a range of known grammar
  and vocabulary. A key focus is revisiting prepositions of place and movement,
  consolidating past participle knowledge and contrasting present and perfect
  tenses.Inversion questions are also practised."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this module pupils build on previous knowledge of the perfect tense in
  understanding key periods of France's history and achievements. Irregular past participles
  are revisited, and sound-symbol correspondences practised to consolidate on the grammar
  points covered, for example nasal and non-nasal vowels to link to the past participles ending
  in 'i' and 'u'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2865-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2865-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2865-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2865-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2865-5 ;
  curric:id "2865"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.012742Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-2859
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Routines: numbers 32-69, time"@en ;
  curric:slug "routines-numbers-32-69-time" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils consolidate and extend their knowledge of numbers from 32-69
  and use the impersonal verb 'il est' to tell the time. Avoir and être are revisited to
  talk about feelings and states. Knowledge of question forms and present and perfect tenses
  is deepened in writing and speaking."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils apply their existing and new knowledge in talking
  about their day. Applying number rules and telling the time adds depth and further practice
  opportunities for pupils' dialogues and conversations. Pupils also apply their knowledge of
  avoir and être in expressing feelings and states. This is brought together in an extended
  writing task, allowing pupils to demonstrate their knowledge of grammar and high frequency
  vocabulary with increasing confidence, fluency and personalisation.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2859-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2859-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2859-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2859-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2859-5 ;
  curric:id "2859"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.014714Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having .

oakcurric:unit-2843
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Past experiences: -ER verbs in the present and past"@en ;
  curric:slug "past-experiences-er-verbs-in-the-present-and-past" ;
  rdfs:comment """The perfect tense with 'avoir' for -er verbs, faire and dire is extended for all
  singular forms. Intonation and 'est-ce que' questions and negation in the present and
  perfect tenses are practised, and 'il y a' is contrasted with 'il y avait'. Open eu,oeu,
  open o and closed o,ô are taught."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils anchor their knowledge of the present tense and
  extend their knowledge of the perfect tense with 'avoir' in all singular forms for -er verbs.
  Revisiting the key verb patterns with new verbs is essential to securing the knowledge and
  its applicability in a new context. The cultural background of Belgium and Switzerland adds
  context and awareness. Communicative competence is enhanced as pupils ask and answer
  questions in the present and past tenses and extend descriptions of places in the present and
  past with 'il y a' and 'il y avait' and""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2843-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2843-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2843-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2843-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2843-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2843-6 ;
  curric:id "2843"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.053635Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2849
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Language learning: plural -RE verbs in the present"@en ;
  curric:slug "language-learning-plural-re-verbs-in-the-present" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils consolidate and extend their knowledge of -re verbs,
  examining verbs like entendre, lire and écrire in the present tense. Verbs with à or de
  before a noun are also revisited together with intonation and inversion question formation
  with and without question words."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate and extend their knowledge of -re verbs,
  examining verbs like entendre, lire and écrire in the present tense. Verbs with à or de
  before a noun are also practised. Revisiting key verb patterns with new verbs is essential to
  securing this knowledge. It also provides rich context here as pupils apply their knowledge
  in the context of language learning, school trips and interviews. Plentiful practice with
  high frequency vocabulary extends communicative range and competence.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2849-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2849-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2849-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2849-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2849-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2849-6 ;
  curric:id "2849"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.056136Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2835
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My plans: aller + infinitive"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-plans-aller-plus-infinitive" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use 'aller' plus infinitive to express future intentions for
  weekend and holiday plans. Knowledge of negation is extended to include two-verb
  structures and inversion questions are practised in two-verb structures. The SSCS qu and j
  are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils continue to expand their verb lexicon and knowledge of
  two-verb structures. The irregular verb 'partir' is introduced as pupils discuss holiday
  plans. 'Aller' plus infinitive is introduced as pupils express their future intentions.
  Negation and inversion questions are also revisited, this time with two-verb structures so
  that pupils can extend their knowledge of these structures with a future tense.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2835-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2835-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2835-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2835-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2835-5 ;
  curric:id "2835"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.101787Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-2839
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Celebrations and festivals: numbers, dates, 'on' in present tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "celebrations-and-festivals-numbers-dates-on-in-present-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils revisit -er verbs and question words with 'est-ce que in contrast to
  intonation and inversion questions. They learn numbers 13-31, use the pronoun 'on' meaning
  'people, you, one'. Possessive adjectives now include son,sa,ses and notre,nos. The SSCs
  em,am, aim,im and om are practised."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' previous knowledge of questions and answers,
  with question words now added to the 'est-ce que' structure. Knowledge of -er verbs is
  embedded in the context of celebrations as pupils prepare interview questions for
  celebrities, and talk about how and when people celebrate cultural events in France and
  family birthdays. Possessive adjectives are revisited and extended with questions and answers
  on birthdays which develop pupil's communicative skills and confidence.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2839-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2839-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2839-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2839-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2839-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2839-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2839-7 ;
  curric:id "2839"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.110179Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2828
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Everyday situations: plural 'faire'"@en ;
  curric:slug "everyday-situations-plural-faire" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils expand their core verb lexicon with plural forms of 'faire'.
  With existing and new high frequency vocabulary, they apply this to say what people do in
  everyday situations. They learn some possessive adjectives and revisit intonation
  questions. Several SSC are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate their verb knowledge further by
  revisiting and extending their knowledge of 'faire' with plural persons. Pupils have the
  opportunity to cement their knowledge in paired speaking and writing activities. After the
  introduction of possessive adjectives, pupils reactivate their knowledge of singular and
  plural nouns and adjectives. Intonation questions are embedded as pupils revisit high
  frequency vocabulary when talking about family.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2828-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2828-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2828-3 ,
