oakcurric:unit-2829
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Places to go: singular 'aller'"@en ;
  curric:slug "places-to-go-singular-aller" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn the highly frequent verb 'aller' in all forms. Talking
  of going to places, they learn the forms of 'à' meaning 'to'. Practice of intonation
  questions is expanded with the question words 'où', 'comment' and 'quand'. Silent final e
  and é (-er, -ez) are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils expand their verb lexicon with the highly frequent
  'aller' firstly in singular forms, which are then revisited and extended with the plural
  forms. . The lesson provides multiple opportunities to consolidate the verb with the options
  for 'to' - à la/au/à l'/aux. These options are practised in both question and answer form,
  with additional question words 'où', 'quand' and 'comment'. Students are given plentiful
  practice opportunities for consolidation and the number of components they are combining in
  their conversations increased.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2829-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2829-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2829-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2829-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2829-5 ;
  curric:id "2829"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.140134Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-use-reference-resources ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2848
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Friends and family: comparison with adjectives and adverbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "friends-and-family-comparison-with-adjectives-and-adverbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils extend their knowledge of feminine adjective agreement before
  then learning the comparative forms of adjectives and adverbs and exploring these in
  comparative structures 'plus...que', 'moins...que' and 'aussi...que. Pupils learn the SSCs
  om,on and um,un before a vowel."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils extend their narrative and descriptive competence
  with the introduction of comparative adjectives and adverbs. Previous units have consolidated
  adjective agreement and placement and adverb placement rules. This unit allows pupils to
  expand their use of adjectives and adverbs in richer communicative structures in the context
  of experiences and family life.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2848-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2848-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2848-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2848-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2848-5 ;
  curric:id "2848"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.166049Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-2845
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "School life: -IR verbs in the present, uses of 'vous' and 'on'"@en ;
  curric:slug "school-life-ir-verbs-in-the-present-uses-of-vous-and-on" ;
  rdfs:comment """Here pupils extend their knowledge of -ir verbs like sortir and venir and add
  verbs like choisir in all forms. The formal 'vous' and 'on' and the present tense with
  future meaning give pupils more options to talk with others about activities and routines.
  Liaison, elision with h is taught."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate and extend their knowledge of frequent
  irregular -ir verbs like sortir and venir in all forms. Verbs like choisir and finir are also
  learnt in all forms. Pupils extend their communicative competence with formal vs plural
  'vous' and 'on' when asking and answering questions in the context of school exchange and
  school life in general. Pupils develop comprehension skills in listening to longer passages
  on French school life. New vocabulary and the present tense with future meaning supports more
  detailed dialogue on routine and upcoming plans.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2845-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2845-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2845-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2845-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2845-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2845-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2845-7 ;
  curric:id "2845"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.209831Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
