    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2857-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2857-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2857-7 ;
  curric:id "2857"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.283930Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation .

oakcurric:unit-2864
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Future and past events: 2-verb structures with prepositions"@en ;
  curric:slug "future-and-past-events-2-verb-structures-with-prepositions" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils revisit two-verb structures in the present tense as they talk of decisions
  for their future. They apply verbs with à and de before an infinitive, the question word
  quel and demonstrative adjective ce,cet,cette,ces. Impersonal verbs with adjectives + de,
  and weather expressions are practised."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils apply known and new vocabulary and grammar to longer
  texts, conversations and writing tasks as they discuss decisions about their future and
  universal experiences. Two-verb structures are embedded in different context and pupils
  extend their verb lexicon and communicative range by using verbs with à and de before an
  infinitive. A range of impersonal phrases with adjectives and de, including weather
  expressions, give pupils greater range, flexibility and variety in communicating and giving
  opinions in a range of contexts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2864-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2864-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2864-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2864-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2864-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2864-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2864-7 ;
  curric:id "2864"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.286025Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-2823
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities: singular 'faire'"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-singular-faire" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use the highly irregular high frequency verb 'faire' in
  singular persons. They use 'faire' followed by le, la, les and learn the English
  equivalents 'do' and 'make'. Pupils ask and answer questions using the question word
  'quoi'. The SSCs ain/in and è/ê are introduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' previous knowledge of singular and plural
  nouns with the definite articles, which are applied with the highly frequent irregular verb
  faire in singular persons. Pupils practise asking and answering intonation questions, with
  the new question word 'quoi' and a range of new vocabulary to extend their communicate
  competence. Pupils appreciate importance differences in translation, with the English 'do'
  and 'make' as equivalents for 'faire', They also develop confidence in writing as they
  manipulate the verb 'faire' in short sentences.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2823-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2823-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2823-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2823-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2823-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2823-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2823-7 ;
  curric:id "2823"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.458751Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2847
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "New places: modal verbs, aller + infinitive, negation"@en ;
  curric:slug "new-places-modal-verbs-aller-plus-infinitive-negation" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils consolidate their knowledge of modal verbs devoir, vouloir,
  pouvoir and savoir in the present tense singular forms. They also revisit aller with
  infinitive to express future intention and revisit question formation and negation in
  two-verb structures."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils revisit modal verbs in singular form in the context
  of a visit to Paris, and refresh their knowledge of the aller + infinitive in all forms to
  express future intention when planning visits to new places. Revisiting two-verb structures
  with modals and the near future provides further opportunities for pupils to secure this
  knowledge, along with further practice of ne...pas with two-verb structures, question forms
  and adverb placement.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2847-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2847-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2847-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2847-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2847-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2847-6 ;
  curric:id "2847"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.468855Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
