  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-2855
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Music and other cultural events: être, adjectives, -ER verbs, questions"@en ;
  curric:slug "music-and-other-cultural-events-etre-adjectives-er-verbs-questions" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils reactivate their knowledge of être and -er verbs in all forms
  in the present tense. Previously learnt vocabulary is revisited along with 'ne...pas',
  adjective agreement and number patterns and pour and sans with an infinitive."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils refresh their knowledge of the present tense and
  embed it in use with previously learnt grammar and vocabulary to describe themselves and
  others, including their favourite singer or group. Pupils write and talk about cultural
  events, learning about the Dieppe Festival. Revisiting question and answer structures helps
  revise and embed this core conversation thread further.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2855-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2855-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2855-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2855-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2855-5 ,
