oakcurric:unit-2840
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Everyday life: -ER verbs in the present and past"@en ;
  curric:slug "everyday-life-er-verbs-in-the-present-and-past" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, knowledge of -er verbs in the present tense is embedded, and
  intonation and inversion questions with and without question words are revisited. Pupils
  contrast present and perfect tenses with 'avoir' for -er verbs, faire and dire. The SSCs
  um,un and -gn- are taught."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils know the present tense of -er verbs and in this unit they
  consolidate it together with the negative and asking and answering questions. Opportunities
  are provided here to embed this skill in the context of everyday school activities. Pupils
  are then introduced to the perfect tense with avoir (je form) and the formation of regular
  past participles of -er verbs, of faire and dire.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2840-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2840-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2840-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2840-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2840-5 ;
  curric:id "2840"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.567029Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2827
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Family life: numbers, plural nouns, plural 'avoir' & 'être'"@en ;
  curric:slug "family-life-numbers-plural-nouns-plural-avoir-and-etre" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils extend their knowledge of 'être'and 'avoir' to include plural forms. 'il y
  a' is introduced with numbers and nouns. Pupils consolidate regular plural 's' on nouns
  and adjectives, adjective agreement and indefinite articles, including the plural 'des'.
  Sound spelling links are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit further expands pupils' verb lexicon with plural forms of avoir
  and être. Revisiting the key irregular verb patterns before extending them is essential to
  embed the core knowledge. Pupils also consolidate their knowledge of noun and adjective
  plurals and agreement, and the use of indefinite articles. This is applied to speaking and
  listening pairwork, and photo descriptions to consolidate communicative competence.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2827-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2827-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2827-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2827-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2827-5 ;
  curric:id "2827"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.644604Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having .

oakcurric:unit-2846
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "In the news: plural adjectives"@en ;
  curric:slug "in-the-news-plural-adjectives" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils extend their knowledge of plural formation for nouns and
  adjectives. They refresh their knowledge on adjectives before and after the nouns. The
  positioning of multiple adjectives is practised as is the use of very frequent adjectives,
  même, autre and plusieurs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on known high frequency vocabulary and known
  tenses as they extend their knowledge with new rules on plural forms of nouns and adjectives.
  This provides multiple opportunities to practise comprehension, speaking and writing skills
  as they read articles and describe a photo. They practise positioning multiple adjectives as
  they extend their narrative competence in the context of journalism.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2846-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2846-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2846-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2846-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2846-5 ;
  curric:id "2846"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.672905Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order .

oakcurric:unit-2834
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Paris and Nice: adjective placement"@en ;
  curric:slug "paris-and-nice-adjective-placement" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn and practise the position of certain common adjectives
  before the noun. They practise irregular feminine forms of some high frequency adjectives.
  Pupils also revisit ç and soft c and a range of other SSCs as they revisit high frequency
  vocabulary in describing places."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils embed and secure knowledge of common irregular verbs.
  They refresh their knowledge of adjectival agreement and learn irregular feminine forms of
  some high frequency adjectives. Word order variations are introduced with the pre-nominal
  position of certain common adjectives. Revisiting high frequency vocabulary, high-frequency
  irregular verbs, two verb structures and sound-symbol correspondences, this unit anchors core
  knowledge, providing practice in listening, speaking, reading, translation and writing as
  pupils develop comprehension skills and communicative competence.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2834-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2834-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2834-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2834-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2834-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2834-6 ;
  curric:id "2834"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.674781Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
