oakcurric:unit-2821
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Belongings: singular 'avoir', nouns and indefinite articles"@en ;
  curric:slug "belongings-singular-avoir-nouns-and-indefinite-articles" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils are introduced to the singular forms of 'avoir' as they
  describe possessions. Indefinite articles and grammatical genders are introduced, along
  with adjectives positioned after the noun. Pupils learn t-liaison and the sound-symbol
  correspondences e, au,eau, u and ou."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils are introduced to the singular persons of the
  irregular and 2nd highest frequency verb 'avoir' to talk about things they and others have.
  The concept of grammatical gender is introduced with the indefinite articles 'un' and 'une' .
  Pupils extend their existing knowledge of adjectives and adjectival agreement with new
  vocabulary and common rule of adjectives after the nouns they describe. Providing
  opportunities to practise asking intonation questions and answering them develops pupils'
  communicative competence and confidence at this early stage of learning.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2821-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2821-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2821-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2821-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2821-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2821-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2821-7 ;
  curric:id "2821"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.810060Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having .

oakcurric:unit-2822
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People: singular 'avoir' and 'être' and definite articles"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-singular-avoir-and-etre-and-definite-articles" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils use the singular forms of 'être' and 'avoir, adjectives and indefinite
  articles to describe a friend. They learn definite articles, plural 's' on nouns, and the
  feminisation of job titles to extend their descriptions. Silent final 'e' and é, (-er and
  -ez) and s-liaison are introduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate their knowledge of avoir and être and
  adjective placement and agreement as they apply it in the context of describing a friend.
  Grammatical gender is reinforced with the introduction of the definite articles, and
  application of nouns and determiners extended with regular plural nouns and 'les'. New
  vocabulary including adverbs and feminine job titles extends pupils' communicative competence
  in writing. It also encourages the development of a personal repertoire as pupils can add
  their own vocabulary to describe a friend.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2822-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2822-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2822-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2822-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2822-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2822-6 ;
  curric:id "2822"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.813134Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-2820
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Greeting: singular  'être' and regular adjectives"@en ;
  curric:slug "greeting-singular-etre-and-regular-adjectives" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils use the singular forms of 'être' in order to meet and greet
  friends and to ask and answer questions. Regular high frequency adjectives in masculine
  and feminine forms are used to describe friends. The Silent Final Consonant is introduced
  along with the SSCs a, i and eu."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces the highly irregular but highest frequency verb
  'être' in singular forms (je, tu, il/elle) for immediate receptive and productive use in
  greetings, basic question (raised intonation form) and answer conversations. The concept of
  adjective agreement is introduced for male and female persons, and will be applied in later
  units to items with the grammatical gender masculine and feminine. This unit also introduces
  the silent final consonant, a prominent feature of French phonics, which will be revisited
  and consolidated frequently in later units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2820-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2820-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2820-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2820-4 ;
  curric:id "2820"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.035118Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-2825
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities: singular verbs in the present tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-singular-verbs-in-the-present-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils revisit the verb faire, with meanings other than 'do' or
  'make'. Pupils use singular forms of -er verbs with new high frequency vocabulary to talk
  about activities. They use two-verb structures with 'aimer' and practise the sound
  spelling links ch, ç, ai, oi, -tion and -ien."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupil's previous knowledge of 'faire' in singular
  persons, expanding their knowledge to include English meanings other than 'do' or 'make'.
  They grow their verb lexicon with singular forms of highly frequent '-er' verbs. They learn
  the two English translations, 'I do' and 'I am doing' for the French present tense, a
  linguistic difference practised frequently in later units. Two-verb structures (introduced
  here with 'aimer' plus infinitive) are consolidated in later units, as are prepositions with
  two meanings (here à for 'at' and 'to').""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2825-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2825-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2825-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2825-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2825-5 ;
  curric:id "2825"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.847240Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-2867
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Ongoing past events: imperfect tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "ongoing-past-events-imperfect-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils re-examine être and avoir in the imperfect tense in singular
  form, and add aller and faire in the imperfect what people used to do. The imperfect is
  then contrasted with the perfect tense to distinguish between ongoing vs specific events.
  The verb 'voir' is introduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this units, pupils revisit known vocabulary and grammar whilst applying
  être and avoir in the imperfect tense. Aller and faire are also practised to discuss habitual
  events which 'used to' happen. When narrating what happened pupils enrich their conversations
  and written production through use of imperfect for ongoing events vs perfect tense for
  specific events. Question words with est-ce que and the imperfect tense are practised.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2867-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2867-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2867-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2867-4 ;
  curric:id "2867"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.965026Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-2824
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Poem: Sept Couleurs Magiques"@en ;
  curric:slug "poem-sept-couleurs-magiques" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils expand their vocabulary with an extended reading text by a
  French poet. They consolidate their knowledge of vocabulary agreement, revisit sound
  symbol correspondences, add new ones (qu, j and soft g) and apply their knowledge in
  creating their own versions of the poem."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit secures pupils' previous knowledge of adjective agreements with
  practice in a culture-rich and creative context. Pupils learn to respond to the text with
  curiosity and persistence as they are supported to apply known and learn new high frequency
  vocabulary in accessible literature. In this scaffolded approach, pupils learn to respond in
  writing, which includes expanding their personal repertoire. In later units they will extend
  this skill, developing confidence in reading (aloud) and responding to more complex texts,
  with a secure foundation in high frequency vocabulary.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2824-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2824-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2824-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2824-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2824-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2824-6 ;
  curric:id "2824"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.996758Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3102
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Say and write new words in French: gender, nouns, alphabet"@en ;
  curric:slug "say-and-write-new-words-in-french-gender-nouns-alphabet" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils revisit and consolidate prior grammar learning, known
  vocabulary and sounds of the language. They specifically revisit articles, gender and
  number, possessive adjectives, il y a, il n'y a pas de and the French alphabet."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils reactivate previous knowledge of the verb avoir, articles, gender,
  number and the alphabet as they practise asking and answering the question 'Comment ça
  s'écrit?'. The context of Francophone countries provides a rich basis for practising
  previously taught sound-symbol correspondences for both written transcription and oral
  practice on spelling place names.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3102-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3102-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3102-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3102-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3102-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3102-6 ;
  curric:id "3102"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.527607Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having .

oakcurric:unit-2826
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities: plural verbs in the present tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-plural-verbs-in-the-present-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils apply and extend their verb knowledge to include the plural
  forms of '-er' verbs.With new high frequency vocabulary they talk, ask and answer
  questions about a broader range of activities in and out of school and in holiday
  activities. They revisit sound spelling links, a and i."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit expands the pupils' verb lexicon with the new high frequency -er
  verbs in all forms. and Doing, using verbs in the present. Providing opportunities to ask and
  answer intonation questions in all verb""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2826-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2826-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2826-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2826-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2826-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2826-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2826-7 ;
  curric:id "2826"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.669290Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-2856
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Future plans and work experience: 2-verb phrases with 'aller', modals, 'il faut'"@en ;
  curric:slug "future-plans-and-work-experience-2-verb-phrases-with-aller-modals-il-faut" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils talk about future intentions using aller with infinitive.
  They also practise this two-verb structure with modal verbs in all persons, as well as
  intonation, est-ce que questions and negation with two-verb structures. Pupils also use
  'il faut,il ne faut pas' with infinitive."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on two-verb structures using aller and infinitive and
  modal verbs with infinitive. Pupils apply known vocabulary in new contexts of future plans,
  and talking and writing about work experience. Pupils now use negation more confidently with
  two-verb structures and add 'il faut/il ne faut pas' to their repertoire in talking about
  rules and expectations at work and preparing for a job interview. Word patterns are
  consolidated and feminine adjective agreement rules extended and cultural enrichment provided
  on the goals and ambitions of a France national team football player.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2856-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2856-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2856-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2856-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2856-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2856-6 ;
  curric:id "2856"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.691443Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-derivational-word-patterns ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-2833
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Everyday life: negation with ne … pas in the present tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "everyday-life-negation-with-ne-pas-in-the-present-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils are introduced to the verb 'dormir' in singular persons.They
  use negation 'ne...pas' with single verb structures and 'ne...pas de' before nouns, as
  they use high frequency vocabulary for activities they don't do or say what isn't in a
  place. SSCs [ai] and [ch] are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils continue to consolidate common irregular -re and -ir
  verbs, and add 'dormir' in singular persons. Revisiting common verb patterns and gradually
  introducing common irregular ones is essential in building and securing this knowledge.
  Negation is introduced, with 'ne...pas' for single verb structures, and 'ne...pas de' before
  a noun with 'il y a', 'avoir, 'être' and 'faire'. Applying known and new vocabulary
  (including prepositions) helps build confidence with the new structures.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2833-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2833-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2833-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2833-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2833-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2833-6 ;
