  'ils/elles' to mean 'it' and they'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.116370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-25482
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use the perfect tense with 'avoir' to talk about what I did yesterday and
  compare it to what I am doing today."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.117344Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-21515
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can recognise when the pronoun 'on' means 'people in general' or 'we' in informal
